Date:  0/0/1982
Source:  Two Hundred Years of NZ Food & Cookery
Author:  BURTON
Vol / Page:  4
Edition:
Quote:  [Title] Kao (sweetmeats) Kao were usually made in the leisure hours after the kumara had been gathered in autumn, ... To prepare kao, select some elongated kumara and with a sharpened manuka stick or knife scrape out the dirt from the eyes. ... Wash the kumara and wrap each in puriri leaves. Place in a slow hangi for 24 hours, then dry in the sun for as long as two weeks
